CHECKING MAP CONTENT

EMPTY_CONTENT = spaces, null char, end of 2d arr meaning e.g. a WALL (1) at the first row after DPS

1. Fionas algo, Depth first search
	1. look for a WALL (1) which is adjacent to a FLOOR (0) -> mark it as START (A)
	2. DPS search clockwise (right, top, down, left)
	3. if one WALL, from DPS, hits the START (A) from the left or bottom its VALID
		a. if INVALID break and return Error
		b. if VALID let flood fill continue and 
		c. check if there are stil WALLS (1) adjacent (ALSO DIAGONALS) by EMPTY_CONTENT(), which havent been marked by DPS

1. Flood fill (OLD)
	a. to check if there are connected spaces from the top to bottom (y = 0 til map_height)
		and from left to right (x = 0 til map_width)
		> yes this also means if there are entire lines of spaces left,rigth,above or under the map
		> use flood fill ONLY on SPACES WHICH ARE (y = 0 or x = 0), no need to check every space
	
